[BILLY] Daddy, I'm scared.

267
00:12:16,805 --> 00:12:18,056
Can we go home?

268
00:12:22,225 --> 00:12:23,537
[DAN] Don't go out there.

269
00:12:23,561 --> 00:12:25,914
There's something in the
mist, it took John Lee!

270
00:12:25,938 --> 00:12:28,083
[MAN] Screw that, I'm
getting in my car.

271
00:12:28,107 --> 00:12:29,460
[DAN] Mister, no!

272
00:12:29,484 --> 00:12:31,796
(SIREN BLARING)

273
00:12:31,820 --> 00:12:34,739
(TIRES SCREECHING)

274
00:12:49,421 --> 00:12:51,757
(SCREAMING)

275
00:12:56,388 --> 00:12:58,223
(DOORS SLAMMING)

276
00:13:02,018 --> 00:13:04,246
Please hold me.

277
00:13:04,270 --> 00:13:05,539
It's okay, it's okay.

278
00:13:05,563 --> 00:13:07,333
[AMBROSE]
It's a pollution cloud,

279
00:13:07,357 --> 00:13:10,170
from the mills, down in
Rumsford.

280
00:13:10,194 --> 00:13:13,781
Some kind of chemical
explosion, has to be.

281
00:13:15,031 --> 00:13:16,117
[OLLIE] What is it?

282
00:13:17,284 --> 00:13:18,577
What's going on?

283
00:13:21,663 --> 00:13:22,748
It's death.

284
00:13:24,042 --> 00:13:29,004
(LOUD RUMBLING)
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

285
00:14:00,830 --> 00:14:02,373
[BILLY] Daddy!

286
00:14:04,585 --> 00:14:06,980
(COUGHING)

287
00:14:07,004 --> 00:14:09,173
(SOBBING)

288
00:14:16,680 --> 00:14:18,933
(COUGHING)

289
00:14:21,728 --> 00:14:23,914
[MIKE] That was an earthquake.

290
00:14:23,938 --> 00:14:26,375
[AMBROSE] I tell ya, the
goddamn mills blew up!

291
00:14:26,399 --> 00:14:28,419
Is everyone okay?

292
00:14:28,443 --> 00:14:29,795
Is anyone hurt?

293
00:14:29,819 --> 00:14:31,130
Everybody just stay put, okay?

294
00:14:31,154 --> 00:14:33,467
Just stay inside the store.

295
00:14:33,491 --> 00:14:34,760
I can't.

296
00:14:34,784 --> 00:14:36,344
I can't stay here, I
gotta get home to my kids.

297
00:14:36,368 --> 00:14:39,430
[MRS. CARMODY] No, no, don't
go out there.

298
00:14:39,454 --> 00:14:41,016
It's death out there.

299
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:41,851
It's the end of days.

300
00:14:41,875 --> 00:14:44,060
Stop it, okay?

301
00:14:44,084 --> 00:14:45,270
Stop it.

302
00:14:45,294 --> 00:14:47,063
Please, everybody,
everybody just relax.

303
00:14:47,087 --> 00:14:47,941
- Okay?
- [BUD] He's right.

304
00:14:47,965 --> 00:14:49,233
Let's just stay cool,

305
00:14:49,257 --> 00:14:50,651
let's just try to figure
out what happened.

306
00:14:50,675 --> 00:14:51,861
I'm sorry.

307
00:14:51,885 --> 00:14:53,403
I can't just stay here,

308
00:14:53,427 --> 00:14:54,988
I have to get home to my kids.

309
00:14:55,012 --> 00:14:57,241
[DAN] Ma'am, no, you
can't go out there.

310
00:14:57,265 --> 00:14:58,993
That could be a poisonous
gas cloud.

311
00:14:59,017 --> 00:15:00,411
Didn't you hear
that man screaming?

312
00:15:00,435 --> 00:15:03,165
I agree, let's stay here
until we figure it out.

313
00:15:03,189 --> 00:15:05,209
You're not listening!

314
00:15:05,233 --> 00:15:06,733
I can't stay here.

315
00:15:08,068 --> 00:15:12,007
Wanda's looking after
little Victor, she's only 8.

316
00:15:12,031 --> 00:15:14,968
Sometimes she forgets she's
supposed to be watching him,

317
00:15:14,992 --> 00:15:15,827
you know?

318
00:15:19,790 --> 00:15:23,393
I told them I'd only
be gone a few minutes.

319
00:15:23,417 --> 00:15:24,502
She's only 8!

320
00:15:26,839 --> 00:15:28,924
For their sakes, don't.

321
00:15:34,763 --> 00:15:37,516
Well, is anybody gonna help me?

322
00:15:40,060 --> 00:15:41,896
[DAVID] Shh, it's okay, pal.

323
00:15:42,981 --> 00:15:46,150
Won't somebody here
see a lady home?

324
00:15:50,446 --> 00:15:51,281
You?

325
00:15:59,373 --> 00:16:00,207
You?

326
00:16:10,217 --> 00:16:11,486
It's okay, buddy.

327
00:16:11,510 --> 00:16:12,322
You?

328
00:16:12,346 --> 00:16:13,990
Ma'am, please.

329
00:16:14,014 --> 00:16:16,682
I got my own boy to worry about.

330
00:16:19,853 --> 00:16:22,081
I hope you all rot in hell.

331
00:16:22,105 --> 00:16:24,608
[OLLIE] Ma'am, please, wait
until...

332
00:16:32,866 --> 00:16:35,369
(EERIE MUSIC)

333
00:16:59,478 --> 00:17:02,164
[BUD] Okay, let's
start cleaning up, okay?

334
00:17:02,189 --> 00:17:05,001
Get the spilled bottles,
broken glass, stuff like that.

335
00:17:05,025 --> 00:17:07,379
Aisle 3 has medical supplies.

336
00:17:07,403 --> 00:17:09,364
Okay, okay, it's okay.

337
00:17:10,615 --> 00:17:12,967
Easy champ, come on.

338
00:17:12,991 --> 00:17:14,553
(BILLY SOBBING)

339
00:17:14,577 --> 00:17:16,055
All right, hey, hey, hey.

340
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:18,182
You can't keep crying
like this, pal.

341
00:17:18,206 --> 00:17:19,683
Come on.

342
00:17:19,707 --> 00:17:21,435
You're gonna hurt yourself.

343
00:17:21,460 --> 00:17:22,604
Come on, you all right?

344
00:17:22,628 --> 00:17:23,730
I want Mommy.

345
00:17:23,754 --> 00:17:24,689
All right, I know you do.

346
00:17:24,713 --> 00:17:25,547
Okay.

347
00:17:27,757 --> 00:17:30,528
Just try to breathe, okay?

348
00:17:30,552 --> 00:17:33,281
Just try to breathe,
pal, it's okay.

349
00:17:33,305 --> 00:17:34,556
It's all right.

350
00:17:36,600 --> 00:17:38,119
I haven't seen him suck
his thumb like this

351
00:17:38,144 --> 00:17:40,247
since he was two years old.

352
00:17:40,271 --> 00:17:42,040
He's in shock.

353
00:17:42,064 --> 00:17:43,708
I think we all are.

354
00:17:43,732 --> 00:17:45,378
You haven't met.

355
00:17:45,402 --> 00:17:46,796
Amanda Dunfrey.

356
00:17:46,820 --> 00:17:50,007
She's new in town
as of this semester.

357
00:17:50,031 --> 00:17:53,387
Teaches 3rd grade, and
the special ed kids

358
00:17:53,411 --> 00:17:55,096
now that Mosher's retired.

359
00:17:55,119 --> 00:17:57,932
She's wonderful,
the kids love her.

360
00:17:57,956 --> 00:18:02,896
And David's an artist, he
does movie posters and such.

361
00:18:02,920 --> 00:18:03,838
Oh, and me.

362
00:18:04,922 --> 00:18:08,069
Lord, I'm babbling away
like some old biddy

363
00:18:08,092 --> 00:18:09,610
at a tea party.

364
00:18:09,635 --> 00:18:11,363
My nerves are jangled, I guess.

365
00:18:11,387 --> 00:18:12,781
Boy settle down?

366
00:18:12,805 --> 00:18:14,116
How is he?

367
00:18:14,139 --> 00:18:15,368
Still hot.

368
00:18:15,392 --> 00:18:17,120
[AMANDA] Why don't I get
him some aspirin?

369
00:18:17,144 --> 00:18:17,788
Aisle 3.

370
00:18:17,812 --> 00:18:19,688
- Okay.
- Thanks.

371
00:18:20,938 --> 00:18:22,166
How's Dan?

372
00:18:22,190 --> 00:18:24,002
Ah, his nose stopped bleeding.

373
00:18:24,025 --> 00:18:26,775
He's calmer now, somebody
gave him a Valium.

374
00:18:27,821 --> 00:18:30,259
I can't believe the
way he ran in here.

375
00:18:30,283 --> 00:18:31,552
Never seen him like that.

376
00:18:31,576 --> 00:18:34,013
I need something
to cover my boy up.

377
00:18:34,037 --> 00:18:35,681
You got any blankets?

378
00:18:35,705 --> 00:18:38,225
Furniture pads, loading dock.

379
00:18:38,249 --> 00:18:39,518
Gonna keep checking on people,

380
00:18:39,542 --> 00:18:41,228
if you need anything,
just holler.

381
00:18:41,252 --> 00:18:42,063
You bet.

382
00:18:42,087 --> 00:18:43,355
Sally, you mind?

383
00:18:43,379 --> 00:18:44,356
Oh, I'd love to.

384
00:18:44,380 --> 00:18:45,859
I really should
help him clean up.

385
00:18:45,883 --> 00:18:47,235
I'll take him.

386
00:18:47,259 --> 00:18:49,195
- Okay.
- Daddy, don't go!

387
00:18:49,219 --> 00:18:50,987
No, I'll be gone two
seconds, Big Bill.

388
00:18:51,012 --> 00:18:52,740
Come on, I'm gonna
get your blanket.

389
00:18:52,764 --> 00:18:56,310
Mrs. Reppler's here,
and so is Mrs. Turman.

390
00:18:57,394 --> 00:18:58,997
I'll be close by, okay?

391
00:18:59,021 --> 00:19:00,624
Don't worry, I'm not far.

392
00:19:00,648 --> 00:19:01,483
Okay?

393
00:19:02,400 --> 00:19:04,152
Let me look at you.

394
00:19:06,277 --> 00:19:07,112
Hm?

395
00:19:09,364 --> 00:19:10,509
[HATTIE] Wanna lie Down?

396
00:19:10,533 --> 00:19:11,344
Yeah.

397
00:19:11,368 --> 00:19:12,636
Yeah.

398
00:19:12,660 --> 00:19:14,013
There you go.

399
00:19:14,037 --> 00:19:15,222
[NORTAN] As soon as it blows
away

400
00:19:15,246 --> 00:19:17,517
we can walk out of
here safe and free,

401
00:19:17,541 --> 00:19:19,101
but we have to be smarter.

402
00:19:19,124 --> 00:19:21,771
The first thing we need to
do is keep our wits about us

403
00:19:21,795 --> 00:19:23,314
and find out what's happening.

404
00:19:23,338 --> 00:19:24,900
[BIKER] Well, how we gonna
do that, my man?

405
00:19:24,923 --> 00:19:27,694
We've got no phone signal,
we've got no radio.

406
00:19:27,718 --> 00:19:29,446
[NORTAN] I'm sure they're
working on those problems

407
00:19:29,470 --> 00:19:30,864
as we speak.

408
00:19:30,888 --> 00:19:32,449
It stands to reason that
restoring communications

409
00:19:32,473 --> 00:19:34,809
would be their top priority.

410
00:19:46,655 --> 00:19:48,907
(COUGHING)

411
00:20:08,678 --> 00:20:09,555
[DAVID] Oh, shit.

412
00:20:12,474 --> 00:20:13,308
Ow!

413
00:20:15,059 --> 00:20:15,893
Shit!

414
00:20:17,187 --> 00:20:18,021
Ah.

415
00:20:20,566 --> 00:20:22,377
God damn it!

416
00:20:22,401 --> 00:20:24,653
(GROANING)

417
00:20:25,530 --> 00:20:27,049
Bitch!

418
00:20:27,073 --> 00:20:28,758
[NORTAN] It's obvious that
we're in some kind of

419
00:20:28,782 --> 00:20:30,260
natural disaster here.

420
00:20:30,284 --> 00:20:31,970
[BIKER] Ain't nothing obvious
bout this sombitch

421
00:20:31,993 --> 00:20:33,514
from where I sit.

422
00:20:33,538 --> 00:20:35,558
[AMBROSE] There ain't nothing
natural about it either.

423
00:20:35,581 --> 00:20:37,350
[BIKER] That's right.

424
00:20:37,375 --> 00:20:39,270
[MRS. CARMODY] It's Judgment
Day, and it's come round at last.

425
00:20:39,294 --> 00:20:41,815
There is nothing more
obvious or natural than that.

426
00:20:41,839 --> 00:20:43,566
[BIKER] Aw, fuck now.

427
00:20:43,590 --> 00:20:45,109
You've done that to yourself

428
00:20:45,133 --> 00:20:47,575
by a life of sin
and disillusion.

429
00:20:59,148 --> 00:21:01,817
(DOOR CREAKING)

430
00:21:27,136 --> 00:21:29,305
(BANGING)

431
00:21:33,769 --> 00:21:34,871
Hey, whoa!

432
00:21:34,895 --> 00:21:35,706
David!

433
00:21:35,729 --> 00:21:37,748
Hey, you guys hear that?

434
00:21:37,773 --> 00:21:38,625
The generator?

435
00:21:38,649 --> 00:21:39,750
We're just gonna check it out.

436
00:21:39,774 --> 00:21:42,503
No, no, I turned
the generator off,

437
00:21:42,527 --> 00:21:44,029
it was backing up.

438
00:21:45,072 --> 00:21:46,841
Nobody else heard that sound?

439
00:21:46,864 --> 00:21:48,508
What sound?

440
00:21:48,533 --> 00:21:52,472
I don't know, like
a weird noise,

441
00:21:52,496 --> 00:21:54,265
back there in the dark.

442
00:21:54,289 --> 00:21:57,394
Like something was
pressing against the door.

443
00:21:57,418 --> 00:22:00,314
Did you hear it before the
lights went out or after?

444
00:22:00,338 --> 00:22:02,149
No, only after.

445
00:22:02,172 --> 00:22:04,444
After, but look,
I heard it, okay?

446
00:22:04,468 --> 00:22:05,612
Nobody's calling you a liar.

447
00:22:05,635 --> 00:22:07,238
That's what it sounds like.

448
00:22:07,262 --> 00:22:09,615
[JIM] No, no, no, no, now
don't be that way, Mr. Drayton.

449
00:22:09,639 --> 00:22:11,742
[JIM] You had a scare, no doubt.

450
00:22:11,766 --> 00:22:13,327
Let's say we all
go check it out.

451
00:22:13,352 --> 00:22:14,186
Here.

452
00:22:20,526 --> 00:22:21,360
Oof.

453
00:22:23,028 --> 00:22:24,172
Man.

454
00:22:24,196 --> 00:22:25,882
It's pretty rank in here.

455
00:22:25,906 --> 00:22:27,092
Myron, go check it out.

456
00:22:27,116 --> 00:22:28,117
[MYRON] All right.

457
00:22:30,828 --> 00:22:32,497
[JIM] Go on, fire it up.

458
00:22:34,832 --> 00:22:37,836
(GENERATOR RUNNING)

459
00:22:41,172 --> 00:22:42,357
(COUGHING)

460
00:22:42,382 --> 00:22:44,302
All right, turn it off!

461
00:22:45,386 --> 00:22:48,364
[MYRON] Holy crow, don't that
stink.

462
00:22:48,388 --> 00:22:49,657
Something's got the exhaust vent

463
00:22:49,681 --> 00:22:51,243
plugged up from the outside.

464
00:22:51,267 --> 00:22:52,493
[NORM] You get it running
long enough

465
00:22:52,518 --> 00:22:53,996
to raise that door a little,

466
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:55,454
I'll go out and clear
whatever's blocking it.

467
00:22:55,479 --> 00:22:56,665
[DAVID] No, no, you can't
do that.

468
00:22:56,689 --> 00:22:57,541
[JIM] Why not?

469
00:22:57,566 --> 00:22:58,876
It's an electric door, right?

470
00:22:58,900 --> 00:23:00,586
[OLLIE] Well, yeah, but
it may not be wise

471
00:23:00,609 --> 00:23:01,838
to send him out there.

472
00:23:01,862 --> 00:23:03,255
[MYRON] Okay, I'll do it.

473
00:23:03,279 --> 00:23:05,382
No, look, it's not about
who goes out there-

474
00:23:05,406 --> 00:23:07,093
- [MYRON] What, don't you
think I can do it?

475
00:23:07,117 --> 00:23:09,887
[NORM] Hey, I want to go,
it was my idea.

476
00:23:09,911 --> 00:23:12,223
[DAVID] Whoa, wait, wait,
just stop, okay?

477
00:23:12,247 --> 00:23:13,350
Jim, right?

478
00:23:13,374 --> 00:23:14,643
Myron?

479
00:23:14,667 --> 00:23:16,269
You guys are...

480
00:23:16,292 --> 00:23:18,146
Well, you don't
seem to understand,

481
00:23:18,170 --> 00:23:19,647
or you're trying
real hard not to.

482
00:23:19,671 --> 00:23:22,318
This isn't an
ordinary mist, okay?

483
00:23:22,341 --> 00:23:24,987
You open that door and
something gets in here-

484
00:23:25,011 --> 00:23:26,269
- Like what?

485
00:23:26,929 --> 00:23:29,117
Well, like whatever
made that noise I heard.

486
00:23:29,140 --> 00:23:30,701
Are you guys being
willfully defense?

487
00:23:30,725 --> 00:23:32,911
Mr. Drayton, you
know, pardon me,

488
00:23:32,935 --> 00:23:36,750
but I'm not convinced
that you heard anything.

489
00:23:36,774 --> 00:23:38,710
I mean, we're not hearing
anything now, right?

490
00:23:38,734 --> 00:23:39,526
Anybody?

491
00:23:40,861 --> 00:23:42,255
See?

492
00:23:42,279 --> 00:23:43,465
(CHUCKLING)

493
00:23:43,489 --> 00:23:46,301
Now, I know, I know,
you're a big shot artist

494
00:23:46,325 --> 00:23:48,762
with connections in New York
and Hollywood and all that,

495
00:23:48,786 --> 00:23:50,513
but that don't make you
better than anybody else,

496
00:23:50,537 --> 00:23:51,640
not in my book.

497
00:23:51,664 --> 00:23:52,891
Hey, I didn't say that.

498
00:23:52,916 --> 00:23:54,185
[JIM] Nor do I like being
talked down to

499
00:23:54,208 --> 00:23:56,145
or called stupid by a
guy who went to college

500
00:23:56,169 --> 00:23:58,021
just 'cause he's
got the jitters.

501
00:23:58,044 --> 00:24:00,358
Fellas, it doesn't even
matter about the generator,

502
00:24:00,381 --> 00:24:01,942
the food will keep without it.

503
00:24:01,966 --> 00:24:04,653
[JIM] Kid, I'm gonna start te
motor, you raise the door,

504
00:24:04,677 --> 00:24:06,322
and you yell out when
you got enough room.

505
00:24:06,346 --> 00:24:07,157
Yeah.

506
00:24:07,180 --> 00:24:07,991
Okay, good.

507
00:24:08,015 --> 00:24:08,849
Wait!

508
00:24:11,267 --> 00:24:12,787
You guys are gonna let
this kid risk his life

509
00:24:12,811 --> 00:24:14,538
over a generator that
doesn't even matter?

510
00:24:14,563 --> 00:24:15,916
Would you just shut
the fuck up already?

511
00:24:15,940 --> 00:24:17,250
[OLLIE] Norm!

512
00:24:17,274 --> 00:24:19,503
[JIM] Listen, Mr. Drayton,
I tell you what.

513
00:24:19,527 --> 00:24:21,421
The next time you
got something to say,

514
00:24:21,445 --> 00:24:23,049
you count your teeth.

515
00:24:23,073 --> 00:24:26,343
Because I'm sick to
death of your bullshit.

516
00:24:26,367 --> 00:24:27,886
All right?

517
00:24:27,910 --> 00:24:28,762
Come on, Myron.

518
00:24:28,786 --> 00:24:29,597
[DAVID] This is crazy!

519
00:24:29,621 --> 00:24:30,931
[OLLIE] Leave 'em be.

520
00:24:30,956 --> 00:24:33,434
What am I, impugning
their manhood or something?

521
00:24:33,458 --> 00:24:35,603
Listen, they've lost
their sense of proportion.

522
00:24:35,627 --> 00:24:37,105
What's going on here?

523
00:24:37,129 --> 00:24:38,565
Out there in the market they
were scared and confused,

524
00:24:38,589 --> 00:24:40,191
in here there's a
problem they can solve.

525
00:24:40,215 --> 00:24:42,318
So, they're goddamn
gonna solve it.

526
00:24:42,342 --> 00:24:43,153
[JIM] Ready, kid?

527
00:24:43,177 --> 00:24:44,320
Let's rock!

