00:37:56,767 --> 00:37:57,767
it's lunacy!

799
00:37:58,726 --> 00:37:59,954
And from the look of it,

800
00:37:59,978 --> 00:38:01,372
the tentacles are coming
out of the beer cans.

801
00:38:01,396 --> 00:38:03,416
All right, Bud, don't
take our word for it.

802
00:38:03,440 --> 00:38:04,275
Go look.

803
00:38:17,664 --> 00:38:19,666
What the hell is that?

804
00:38:25,255 --> 00:38:28,300
(TENTACLES WIGGLING)

805
00:38:31,469 --> 00:38:34,515
(TENTACLES STEAMING)

806
00:38:51,742 --> 00:38:55,849
It appears we may have a
problem of some magnitude here.

807
00:38:59,374 --> 00:39:01,877
(EERIE MUSIC)

808
00:39:24,150 --> 00:39:25,068
Let me...

809
00:39:27,488 --> 00:39:28,989
Help these people.

810
00:39:32,659 --> 00:39:34,662
Let me preach your word.

811
00:39:36,789 --> 00:39:38,791
Let me shine your light.

812
00:39:39,833 --> 00:39:42,897
'Cause they're not all bad.

813
00:39:42,921 --> 00:39:44,756
They can't all be bad.

814
00:39:48,343 --> 00:39:50,845
Some can be saved, can't they?

815
00:39:52,514 --> 00:39:56,434
Yes, some can be brought
to heaven's holy gates

816
00:39:58,312 --> 00:39:59,956
through your grace.

817
00:39:59,980 --> 00:40:01,083
I have to believe that,

818
00:40:01,107 --> 00:40:03,167
though I know most people swim

819
00:40:03,191 --> 00:40:05,361
in a lake of fire forever.

820
00:40:09,281 --> 00:40:11,741
If I can save a few, even one,

821
00:40:15,247 --> 00:40:18,767
then my life will have
counted for something.

822
00:40:18,791 --> 00:40:21,896
I will have pulled my weight,

823
00:40:21,920 --> 00:40:25,358
I will have earned my
place at your side,

824
00:40:25,382 --> 00:40:29,947
I will have served a
purpose here on this earth.

825
00:40:29,971 --> 00:40:31,388
Hello?

826
00:40:41,065 --> 00:40:43,277
(SNIFFLES)

827
00:40:46,779 --> 00:40:48,197
What?

828
00:40:48,823 --> 00:40:51,136
I just need to use the bathroom.

829
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:51,994
Oh.

830
00:40:53,162 --> 00:40:55,497
Okay, well then, have at it.

831
00:40:59,501 --> 00:41:03,505
Ma'am, I just want you
to know that it's okay,

832
00:41:05,716 --> 00:41:07,486
being scared, I mean.

833
00:41:07,510 --> 00:41:11,740
And, well, if you need
a friend, you know,

834
00:41:11,764 --> 00:41:12,907
someone to talk to-

835
00:41:12,931 --> 00:41:15,602
- I have a friend, God up above.

836
00:41:16,978 --> 00:41:18,831
I talk to him every day.

837
00:41:18,855 --> 00:41:21,083
Don't you condescend me.

838
00:41:21,108 --> 00:41:21,960
I'm sorry?

839
00:41:21,984 --> 00:41:22,837
Not ever.

840
00:41:22,861 --> 00:41:25,380
You don't mock me.

841
00:41:25,404 --> 00:41:28,257
That's not what I was doing.

842
00:41:28,281 --> 00:41:30,594
Look, I tell you what.

843
00:41:30,618 --> 00:41:32,762
The day I need a
friend like you,

844
00:41:32,786 --> 00:41:34,181
I'll just have
myself a little squat

845
00:41:34,205 --> 00:41:35,623
and shit one out.

846
00:41:40,045 --> 00:41:41,271
(AMANDA GASPS)

847
00:41:41,295 --> 00:41:43,273
Maybe you do believe this,

848
00:41:43,297 --> 00:41:46,611
maybe they're not lies,
they're delusions, whatever.

849
00:41:46,635 --> 00:41:49,405
The fact remains the
evidence here is flimsy,

850
00:41:49,429 --> 00:41:50,323
it's bordering on ludicrous.

851
00:41:50,348 --> 00:41:52,451
Hey, this isn't a court room.

852
00:41:52,475 --> 00:41:53,452
You're not arguing a case,

853
00:41:53,476 --> 00:41:54,578
and you're doing
nothing but damage

854
00:41:54,602 --> 00:41:55,745
talking the way you are.

855
00:41:55,769 --> 00:41:56,871
And you can throw
as much cow's blood

856
00:41:56,895 --> 00:41:58,039
around the loading
dock as you want to,

857
00:41:58,063 --> 00:41:59,666
you still haven't fooled anyone.

858
00:41:59,690 --> 00:42:00,627
[OLLIE] Leave it alone, David.

859
00:42:00,651 --> 00:42:01,960
You can't convince some people

860
00:42:01,984 --> 00:42:04,588
there's a fire even when
their hair is burning.

861
00:42:04,612 --> 00:42:06,173
Denial is a powerful thing.

862
00:42:06,197 --> 00:42:07,342
Well, keep talking.

863
00:42:07,366 --> 00:42:08,302
I'll have no part of it,

864
00:42:08,325 --> 00:42:11,136
nor would any thinking person.

865
00:42:11,160 --> 00:42:13,805
Keep thinking, Mr. Lawyer.

866
00:42:13,829 --> 00:42:16,518
There's no defense
against the will of God.

867
00:42:16,542 --> 00:42:19,270
There's no court
of appeals in hell.

868
00:42:19,294 --> 00:42:21,231
There's no defense here either,

869
00:42:21,255 --> 00:42:23,775
not even with all the
fertilizer in the world.

870
00:42:23,799 --> 00:42:26,110
Not even if you stack
it as high as you can,

871
00:42:26,133 --> 00:42:28,780
it's still just bags
of shit, isn't it?

872
00:42:28,804 --> 00:42:30,950
Those of you who want to
discuss this thing rationally

873
00:42:30,974 --> 00:42:34,745
to find a means of rescue
are welcome to join me.

874
00:42:34,769 --> 00:42:39,315
Those who want to stack dog
food, knock yourselves out.

875
00:42:43,152 --> 00:42:45,382
We got those windows
taped up as best we could,

876
00:42:45,405 --> 00:42:46,675
it should help.

877
00:42:46,699 --> 00:42:48,284
Yeah, I think so.

878
00:42:49,910 --> 00:42:52,412
Duct tape and dog food bags.

879
00:42:54,081 --> 00:42:55,642
That bad?

880
00:42:55,666 --> 00:42:56,977
It's not good.

881
00:42:57,001 --> 00:43:00,940
There's none so blind as
those who will not see.

882
00:43:00,964 --> 00:43:02,607
Open your eyes.

883
00:43:02,632 --> 00:43:04,985
Let the scales fall away.

884
00:43:05,009 --> 00:43:07,177
This has all been written.

885
00:43:08,638 --> 00:43:10,640
Revelations, chapter 15.

886
00:43:12,058 --> 00:43:14,495
"And the temple was
filled with smoke

887
00:43:14,519 --> 00:43:18,000
from the glory of God,
and from his power.

888
00:43:18,024 --> 00:43:19,875
And no one could
enter the temple

889
00:43:19,899 --> 00:43:22,712
until the seven plagues
of the seven angels

890
00:43:22,736 --> 00:43:24,214
were completed."

891
00:43:24,238 --> 00:43:26,090
Well, what are you saying?

892
00:43:26,115 --> 00:43:27,467
What are you proposing?

893
00:43:27,491 --> 00:43:32,265
That we all prepare
to meet our maker.

894
00:43:32,289 --> 00:43:35,017
Oh, prepare to meet shit.

895
00:43:35,041 --> 00:43:37,519
Lady, your tongue must
be hung in the middle

896
00:43:37,543 --> 00:43:39,647
so that it could
waggle at both ends.

897
00:43:39,671 --> 00:43:41,566
No, the end time has come.

898
00:43:41,590 --> 00:43:43,609
Not in flames, but in mist.

899
00:43:43,634 --> 00:43:44,528
Come here!

900
00:43:44,552 --> 00:43:45,695
Easy, man!

901
00:43:45,719 --> 00:43:47,655
How about if your
ass prepares to meet

902
00:43:47,679 --> 00:43:49,866
my size 10 work
boot, how bout that?

903
00:43:49,890 --> 00:43:51,618
Hey, there's no call for that.

904
00:43:51,642 --> 00:43:53,953
Yeah, Myron, please,
calm your friend down.

905
00:43:53,977 --> 00:43:56,081
[MRS. CARMODY] I'm trying to
save your soul, you stupid man.

906
00:43:56,105 --> 00:43:57,291
Doubters will doubt till
the end.

907
00:43:57,315 --> 00:43:58,733
Don't worry, Billy, it's okay.

908
00:43:59,108 --> 00:44:03,422
A monstrosity did pull
that poor boy away.

909
00:44:03,446 --> 00:44:05,174
Things in the mist.

910
00:44:05,197 --> 00:44:06,925
Do you doubt?

911
00:44:06,949 --> 00:44:07,985
Do you?

912
00:44:09,453 --> 00:44:10,454
Then go out.

913
00:44:11,538 --> 00:44:13,850
Go out and say "How do you do?"

914
00:44:13,874 --> 00:44:15,208
Shut up, lady!

915
00:44:16,793 --> 00:44:18,021
For God's sakes!

916
00:44:18,044 --> 00:44:18,939
Look, you'll have to stop now,

917
00:44:18,963 --> 00:44:20,023
you're scaring the children.

918
00:44:20,047 --> 00:44:22,108
They should be scared.

919
00:44:22,131 --> 00:44:23,801
Oh yes, they should.

920
00:44:25,428 --> 00:44:28,074
Their beautiful,
pure little minds

921
00:44:28,098 --> 00:44:31,326
have been corrupted
with lies, lies.

922
00:44:31,350 --> 00:44:34,771
All this talk of a
modern God, or no God.

923
00:44:36,606 --> 00:44:38,376
There is one God.

924
00:44:38,400 --> 00:44:40,253
The God of the Israelites.

925
00:44:40,277 --> 00:44:42,880
And he is a stern
and vengeful God.

926
00:44:42,904 --> 00:44:45,507
And we have been mocking
him far too long.

927
00:44:45,532 --> 00:44:49,304
And now he demands
retribution and blood.

928
00:44:49,328 --> 00:44:52,516
It is time to
declare yourselves.

929
00:44:52,540 --> 00:44:55,687
Take sides, the
saved and the damned.

930
00:44:55,710 --> 00:45:00,065
Read the Good Book, it
calls for expiation, blood!

931
00:45:00,089 --> 00:45:01,024
What?

932
00:45:01,048 --> 00:45:01,882
Blood.

933
00:45:03,343 --> 00:45:05,113
Little Normie was first,

934
00:45:05,137 --> 00:45:08,366
and now God calls
the rest of us.

935
00:45:08,390 --> 00:45:09,784
The bill is due.

936
00:45:09,808 --> 00:45:11,369
It must be paid.

937
00:45:11,393 --> 00:45:14,497
As Abraham prepared to
sacrifice his only son

938
00:45:14,521 --> 00:45:16,082
to prove his love for God, so...

939
00:45:16,105 --> 00:45:19,277
- (LOUD SLAP)
- Enough.

940
00:45:23,740 --> 00:45:25,842
Another down payment.

941
00:45:25,866 --> 00:45:27,428
A few more pennies in the jar.

942
00:45:27,452 --> 00:45:28,721
Now that's nice.

943
00:45:28,745 --> 00:45:30,556
See, I can't smack her,
but it's okay for you?

944
00:45:30,580 --> 00:45:32,599
I'm sorry everybody, but
this lady's perspective

945
00:45:32,623 --> 00:45:34,978
is a little too Old
Testament for my tastes.

946
00:45:35,002 --> 00:45:37,564
They'll come for you.

947
00:45:37,587 --> 00:45:40,423
Maybe tonight when
darkness comes.

948
00:45:41,508 --> 00:45:43,236
They'll come tonight.

949
00:45:43,260 --> 00:45:45,238
And they'll take someone else.

950
00:45:45,261 --> 00:45:46,990
See if they don't.

951
00:45:47,014 --> 00:45:50,185
And when they do,
you will cry to God,

952
00:45:51,352 --> 00:45:54,998
and you will beg Mother
Carmody to show you the way.

953
00:45:55,022 --> 00:45:56,190
That's fine.

954
00:45:57,317 --> 00:45:59,545
Until then if you don't shut up,

955
00:45:59,569 --> 00:46:01,756
I'll wrap this tape
around your mouth.

956
00:46:01,780 --> 00:46:04,091
You just try it, Ollie Weeks.

957
00:46:04,115 --> 00:46:05,367
And you, bitch.

958
00:46:06,785 --> 00:46:09,287
You hit me again, if you dare.

959
00:46:11,831 --> 00:46:16,253
You'll be on your knees to
me before this is through.

960
00:46:21,258 --> 00:46:22,819
Those of you who aren't
locals should know

961
00:46:22,843 --> 00:46:27,950
that Mrs. Carmody is known
in town for being unstable.

962
00:46:27,974 --> 00:46:28,767
No shit.

963
00:46:29,893 --> 00:46:31,978
What was your first clue?

964
00:46:36,858 --> 00:46:38,418
Hi.

965
00:46:38,443 --> 00:46:40,087
Sup, little dude?

966
00:46:40,110 --> 00:46:41,923
How come your friends
don't come get us?

967
00:46:41,947 --> 00:46:44,885
They got tanks and stuff, right?

968
00:46:44,909 --> 00:46:46,512
Why can't you just call 'em?

969
00:46:46,536 --> 00:46:47,805
Phones don't work.

970
00:46:47,829 --> 00:46:49,555
But don't you got like a radio?

971
00:46:49,579 --> 00:46:51,099
Hey champ, what's going on?

972
00:46:51,123 --> 00:46:53,018
I want their friends
to come rescue us.

973
00:46:53,042 --> 00:46:53,977
They would if they could, pal,

974
00:46:54,002 --> 00:46:55,479
they're stuck here just like us.

975
00:46:55,503 --> 00:46:56,563
- But-
- Shh.

976
00:46:56,587 --> 00:46:58,525
Guys, we could use
a hand over there.

977
00:46:58,549 --> 00:46:59,400
Yeah, sure thing.

978
00:46:59,425 --> 00:47:01,402
Troop, off your asses.

979
00:47:01,426 --> 00:47:02,278
You all right?

980
00:47:02,302 --> 00:47:04,279
I don't like that scary lady.

981
00:47:04,303 --> 00:47:06,741
Oh, man, I don't either.

982
00:47:06,765 --> 00:47:08,743
But you know what?

983
00:47:08,766 --> 00:47:10,686
Maybe she's scared too.

984
00:47:11,520 --> 00:47:12,353
You think?

985
00:47:13,857 --> 00:47:15,942
You think Mommy's okay?

986
00:47:17,525 --> 00:47:18,360
Billy...

987
00:47:21,573 --> 00:47:23,676
I'm sorry about the
times I was bad to her.

988
00:47:23,700 --> 00:47:24,794
Oh, hey.

989
00:47:25,743 --> 00:47:28,596
Mommy loves you very much,

990
00:47:28,831 --> 00:47:30,582
and I bet she's fine.

991
00:47:32,500 --> 00:47:35,979
And I promise you, I'm
gonna do everything I can

992
00:47:36,004 --> 00:47:37,840
to get us back to her.

993
00:47:38,883 --> 00:47:39,884
- Okay?
- Okay.

994
00:47:41,218 --> 00:47:42,219
- Yeah?
- Yeah.

995
00:47:44,139 --> 00:47:46,408
So we can use the charcoal fluid

996
00:47:46,431 --> 00:47:47,993
and the mops to make torches,

997
00:47:48,017 --> 00:47:50,245
and we've got knives
and stuff, God knows.

998
00:47:50,268 --> 00:47:51,956
This may be a silly
question, Bud,

999
00:47:51,980 --> 00:47:56,377
but do you happen to
have a gun in the store?

1000
00:47:56,401 --> 00:47:57,211
Here?

1001
00:47:57,235 --> 00:47:58,088
No.

1002
00:47:58,112 --> 00:47:59,714
Please, this isn't Los Angeles.

1003
00:47:59,738 --> 00:48:02,163
I've got a shotgun in my truck.

1004
00:48:02,949 --> 00:48:04,594
I could try for it if you want.

1005
00:48:04,618 --> 00:48:05,470
Oh God, I don't
think that would be

1006
00:48:05,494 --> 00:48:06,762
a good idea, Mr. Cornell.

1007
00:48:06,786 --> 00:48:07,622
Hold on.

1008
00:48:10,416 --> 00:48:13,084
This gun, uh, my husband's idea.

1009
00:48:14,169 --> 00:48:16,064
He's away on business a lot.

1010
00:48:16,087 --> 00:48:17,107
It's not even loaded.

1011
00:48:17,131 --> 00:48:19,884
Ain't much use unloaded, ma'am.

1012
00:48:23,555 --> 00:48:24,949
You know how to use that?

1013
00:48:24,972 --> 00:48:27,034
Well, I shot it once
on a pistol range,

1014
00:48:27,058 --> 00:48:29,036
hit the target a few times.

1015
00:48:29,060 --> 00:48:30,896
So, we've got a gun.

1016
00:48:32,105 --> 00:48:34,167
Anybody know how to shoot it?

1017
00:48:34,191 --> 00:48:35,585
Well, I mean?

1018
00:48:35,608 --> 00:48:36,443
I do.

1019
00:48:39,113 --> 00:48:39,948
You?

1020
00:48:41,365 --> 00:48:42,532
Ollie, please.

1021
00:48:48,790 --> 00:48:50,392
Some target shooting.

1022
00:48:50,416 --> 00:48:52,185
State champion in '94.

1023
00:48:52,210 --> 00:48:54,022
Hey, you're crazy
if you go out there.

1024
00:48:54,046 --> 00:48:55,105
Let us pass!

1025
00:48:55,129 --> 00:48:56,315
Let us pass, please!

1026
00:48:56,339 --> 00:48:57,650
Let's just talk
this thing through.

1027
00:48:57,674 --> 00:48:59,193
[NORTON] We have, and we
made our decision.

1028
00:48:59,217 --> 00:49:00,528
We're leaving.

1029
00:49:00,552 --> 00:49:01,905
Hey, Mr. Mackey's gonna
barbecue some chicken

1030
00:49:01,929 --> 00:49:02,823
on the gas grill.

1031
00:49:02,847 --> 00:49:04,074
Why don't we just sit down and-

1032
00:49:04,098 --> 00:49:05,407
- What, and let you
keep on talking?

1033
00:49:05,432 --> 00:49:06,660
No, I've been in far
too many court rooms

1034
00:49:06,684 --> 00:49:07,744
to fall for that.

1035
00:49:07,768 --> 00:49:09,537
You've already psyched out
half a dozen of my people already.

1036
00:49:09,561 --> 00:49:10,622
Your people?

1037
00:49:10,646 --> 00:49:11,499
What kind of talk is that?

1038
00:49:11,523 --> 00:49:12,916
They are people, that's all.

1039
00:49:12,940 --> 00:49:14,292
Now, listen everyone.

1040
00:49:14,316 --> 00:49:17,504
We are experiencing
some kind of disaster.

1041
00:49:17,529 --> 00:49:19,131
I don't know whether
it's man-made or natural,

1042
00:49:19,155 --> 00:49:23,386
but I do know that it's
definitely not supernatural,

1043
00:49:23,410 --> 00:49:24,387
or Biblical.

1044
00:49:24,411 --> 00:49:25,596
And no offense, Mrs. Carmody,

1045
00:49:25,620 --> 00:49:27,139
but the only way we're
gonna help ourselves

1046
00:49:27,163 --> 00:49:28,665
is to seek rescue.

1047
00:49:31,085 --> 00:49:32,420
We're going out.

1048
00:49:34,714 --> 00:49:35,816
Brent, look.

1049
00:49:35,840 --> 00:49:36,733
I'm not discussing
this any further.

1050
00:49:36,757 --> 00:49:37,734
I know.

1051
00:49:37,758 --> 00:49:40,529
I just want to ask a favor.

1052
00:49:40,553 --> 00:49:42,698
Tie this around your waist.

1053
00:49:42,722 --> 00:49:43,907
What for?

1054
00:49:43,931 --> 00:49:47,829
It'll let us know you
got at least 300 feet.

1055
00:49:47,852 --> 00:49:48,937
I'll do it.

1056
00:49:50,354 --> 00:49:51,915
Are you throwing in with them?

1057
00:49:51,938 --> 00:49:52,750
Me?

1058
00:49:52,774 --> 00:49:54,168
No thanks.

1059
00:49:54,192 --> 00:49:56,838
I think your man there's a
little too tightly wound.

