maybe that's for the best.

1328
01:07:07,827 --> 01:07:11,516
I saw creatures fly
into the store tonight,

1329
01:07:11,540 --> 01:07:13,291
they shouldn't exist.

1330
01:07:14,417 --> 01:07:17,351
I keep thinking I'm gonna
wake up in a rubber room.

1331
01:07:18,506 --> 01:07:20,608
You're not alone in that.

1332
01:07:20,632 --> 01:07:22,582
We're all right there with you.

1333
01:07:23,553 --> 01:07:25,671
This isn't gonna end, is it?

1334
01:07:28,145 --> 01:07:29,400
[OLLIE] David.

1335
01:07:30,351 --> 01:07:32,770
It's Joe, he's getting worse.

1336
01:07:51,582 --> 01:07:52,416
Joe.

1337
01:07:54,252 --> 01:07:57,022
How you holdin' up, partner?

1338
01:07:57,046 --> 01:07:59,299
[JOE] David, is that you?

1339
01:08:00,632 --> 01:08:03,320
Yeah, pal, how are doin'?

1340
01:08:03,344 --> 01:08:05,906
It's bad, he's bad.

1341
01:08:05,930 --> 01:08:09,034
I didn't know anything
could hurt like this.

1342
01:08:09,058 --> 01:08:15,676
If you guys can't help me,
you gotta end it, okay?

1343
01:08:17,776 --> 01:08:20,112
Ollie's got that gun, right?

1344
01:08:21,655 --> 01:08:22,466
Right?

1345
01:08:22,490 --> 01:08:23,925
No, no way.

1346
01:08:23,949 --> 01:08:26,721
[JOE] You can't fuck with
me on this, bro.

1347
01:08:26,745 --> 01:08:28,889
Not with me like this.

1348
01:08:28,913 --> 01:08:29,829
I'll do it.

1349
01:08:30,956 --> 01:08:32,709
Just give me the gun!

1350
01:08:34,628 --> 01:08:35,605
We're not there yet, okay?

1351
01:08:35,629 --> 01:08:36,463
Please!

1352
01:08:37,964 --> 01:08:39,132
Joe, listen.

1353
01:08:40,426 --> 01:08:41,260
Pal.

1354
01:08:42,594 --> 01:08:43,905
We're gonna work something out,

1355
01:08:43,928 --> 01:08:45,698
I just need you to hang
in a little longer, okay?

1356
01:08:45,722 --> 01:08:47,057
Can you do that?

1357
01:08:51,062 --> 01:08:53,397
Stay with him, I'll be back.

1358
01:08:55,776 --> 01:08:58,462
Hattie, I need to
go to the bathroom,

1359
01:08:58,486 --> 01:09:00,237
will you watch Billy?

1360
01:09:01,781 --> 01:09:02,615
Hattie?

1361
01:09:19,300 --> 01:09:21,153
See anything?

1362
01:09:21,177 --> 01:09:24,656
The last of those bugs
went away about four.

1363
01:09:24,680 --> 01:09:25,847
Dawn's coming.

1364
01:09:26,849 --> 01:09:28,285
What's on your mind?

1365
01:09:28,309 --> 01:09:29,227
It's Joe.

1366
01:09:31,104 --> 01:09:32,873
If we don't get him on
some serious antibiotics

1367
01:09:32,897 --> 01:09:34,209
he's gonna die of infection.

1368
01:09:34,233 --> 01:09:36,544
Plus he needs painkillers
in the worst way.

1369
01:09:36,568 --> 01:09:40,714
All we've got here is
liquor and aspirin.

1370
01:09:40,738 --> 01:09:43,260
You thinking about going
to the pharmacy next door?

1371
01:09:43,284 --> 01:09:45,220
Irene Reppler says
they've got Silvadene.

1372
01:09:45,244 --> 01:09:47,222
You know, the stuff
they use in burn wards.

1373
01:09:47,246 --> 01:09:48,348
She knows where they keep it.

1374
01:09:48,372 --> 01:09:49,600
Slow down.

1375
01:09:49,624 --> 01:09:51,143
You can't actually be
thinking of doing this.

1376
01:09:51,167 --> 01:09:53,436
I'm also thinking beyond that.

1377
01:09:53,459 --> 01:09:55,855
We have to get out of here.

1378
01:09:55,879 --> 01:09:57,066
I mean, permanently.

1379
01:09:57,090 --> 01:09:58,150
Why?

1380
01:09:58,174 --> 01:09:59,360
We've got plenty to eat.

1381
01:09:59,384 --> 01:10:00,820
And what happens when
one of those things

1382
01:10:00,844 --> 01:10:02,572
decides to break
through this window?

1383
01:10:02,596 --> 01:10:03,698
I'm talking one of the big ones,

1384
01:10:03,722 --> 01:10:05,325
like the one that killed Norm.

1385
01:10:05,349 --> 01:10:07,118
Yeah, then the
flaming torch idea

1386
01:10:07,142 --> 01:10:08,286
didn't work so well, did it?

1387
01:10:08,310 --> 01:10:11,646
We almost burned the
goddamn store down.

1388
01:10:16,527 --> 01:10:17,695
It's Hattie.

1389
01:10:24,327 --> 01:10:26,138
Here?

1390
01:10:26,162 --> 01:10:28,099
Gently now, gently.

1391
01:10:28,123 --> 01:10:29,624
One, two, three!

1392
01:10:39,718 --> 01:10:42,113
I don't know how long
she was there like that,

1393
01:10:42,136 --> 01:10:43,907
lying there next to us.

1394
01:10:43,931 --> 01:10:46,577
I thought she was sleeping.

1395
01:10:46,601 --> 01:10:48,578
I got my 4-wheel drive.

1396
01:10:48,602 --> 01:10:50,331
It's out there.

1397
01:10:50,355 --> 01:10:52,875
You're talking about leaving?

1398
01:10:52,899 --> 01:10:56,670
Well, we should hit
the pharmacy first.

1399
01:10:56,694 --> 01:10:58,006
We gotta bring back
supplies for the injured.

1400
01:10:58,030 --> 01:11:00,300
I mean, if we don't, Joe
Eagleton's gonna die,

1401
01:11:00,324 --> 01:11:02,344
and we can't let that happen.

1402
01:11:02,368 --> 01:11:03,785
But after that...

1403
01:11:04,619 --> 01:11:06,306
Look, my Land Cruiser
can hold eight people.

1404
01:11:06,330 --> 01:11:08,183
I say we drive south as
far as the fuel takes us

1405
01:11:08,207 --> 01:11:10,486
and try to keep
clear of this mist.

1406
01:11:11,001 --> 01:11:12,259
That's it?

1407
01:11:12,795 --> 01:11:14,315
That's the plan?

1408
01:11:14,339 --> 01:11:15,358
That's what I got.

1409
01:11:15,382 --> 01:11:16,691
No, you can't mean it.

1410
01:11:16,714 --> 01:11:17,942
Not after what happened
to Norton and his group.

1411
01:11:17,966 --> 01:11:19,152
No, no, no.

1412
01:11:19,176 --> 01:11:20,653
Amanda, think.

1413
01:11:20,677 --> 01:11:23,074
Norton got over 200
feet from this store,

1414
01:11:23,098 --> 01:11:24,700
that's how much rope played out.

1415
01:11:24,724 --> 01:11:27,244
I'm parked half that
distance from here.

1416
01:11:27,268 --> 01:11:29,247
But who knows how far
this mist has spread.

1417
01:11:29,271 --> 01:11:30,748
It could be the entire
eastern seaboard.

1418
01:11:30,772 --> 01:11:32,958
Yeah, it could be the whole
world for all we know,

1419
01:11:32,982 --> 01:11:36,463
wouldn't make us any
less dead, now would it?

1420
01:11:36,487 --> 01:11:39,216
We have 1 gun, how many rounds?

1421
01:11:39,240 --> 01:11:40,216
We got 10 left.

1422
01:11:40,241 --> 01:11:41,510
10 rounds, Jesus.

1423
01:11:41,534 --> 01:11:43,636
Okay, so 10.

1424
01:11:44,162 --> 01:11:46,223
Want another reason to
get the hell outta here?

1425
01:11:46,247 --> 01:11:47,798
I'll give you the best one.

1426
01:11:48,499 --> 01:11:49,332
Her.

1427
01:11:50,501 --> 01:11:52,271
Mrs. Carmody.

1428
01:11:52,295 --> 01:11:55,108
She's our very own Jim Jones.

1429
01:11:55,132 --> 01:11:56,525
I'd like to leave
before people start

1430
01:11:56,550 --> 01:11:57,693
drinking the Kool-Aid.

1431
01:11:57,717 --> 01:11:59,112
He's right.

1432
01:11:59,136 --> 01:12:01,114
The flakier people get, the
better she's gonna look.

1433
01:12:01,138 --> 01:12:02,198
No, I don't buy that.

1434
01:12:02,222 --> 01:12:03,908
It's obvious she's nuts.

1435
01:12:03,931 --> 01:12:05,201
Look, a few people, maybe.

1436
01:12:05,225 --> 01:12:06,036
But-

1437
01:12:06,060 --> 01:12:07,037
No, I count 4.

1438
01:12:07,061 --> 01:12:07,872
She's preaching
to 'em right now.

1439
01:12:07,896 --> 01:12:09,331
By noon, she'll have 4 more.

1440
01:12:09,355 --> 01:12:11,959
By tomorrow night, when
those things come back,

1441
01:12:11,983 --> 01:12:13,167
she'll have a congregation,

1442
01:12:13,190 --> 01:12:15,337
and then we can
start worrying about

1443
01:12:15,361 --> 01:12:18,465
who she's gonna sacrifice
to make it all better.

1444
01:12:18,489 --> 01:12:19,323
Hm?

1445
01:12:20,283 --> 01:12:21,284
You, Amanda?

1446
01:12:22,286 --> 01:12:23,680
My little boy?

1447
01:12:23,704 --> 01:12:25,306
[DAN] He's right.

1448
01:12:25,330 --> 01:12:28,684
You don't have much faith
in humanity, do you?

1449
01:12:28,708 --> 01:12:29,853
None whatsoever.

1450
01:12:29,877 --> 01:12:31,354
I can't accept that.

1451
01:12:31,378 --> 01:12:34,065
People are basically
good, decent.

1452
01:12:34,089 --> 01:12:36,359
My God, David, we're
a civilized society.

1453
01:12:36,383 --> 01:12:37,945
Sure, as long as the
machines are working

1454
01:12:37,969 --> 01:12:39,280
and you can dial 9-1-1,

1455
01:12:39,304 --> 01:12:40,947
but you take those things away,

1456
01:12:40,971 --> 01:12:42,657
you throw people in the dark,

1457
01:12:42,681 --> 01:12:46,495
you scare the shit outta
them, no more rules.

1458
01:12:46,519 --> 01:12:48,247
You'll see how
primitive they get.

1459
01:12:48,271 --> 01:12:50,958
If you scare people
badly enough,

1460
01:12:50,982 --> 01:12:53,670
you can get 'em to do anything.

1461
01:12:53,694 --> 01:12:57,673
They'll turn to whoever
promises a solution.

1462
01:12:57,697 --> 01:12:58,716
Or whatever.

1463
01:12:58,740 --> 01:13:00,802
Ollie, please, back me up here?

1464
01:13:00,826 --> 01:13:02,636
I wish I could.

1465
01:13:02,661 --> 01:13:05,891
As a species, we're
fundamentally insane.

1466
01:13:05,915 --> 01:13:07,225
Put more than two
of us in a room,

1467
01:13:07,249 --> 01:13:09,102
we pick sides and start
dreaming up reasons

1468
01:13:09,126 --> 01:13:10,794
to kill one another.

1469
01:13:11,921 --> 01:13:14,524
Why'd you think we invented
politics and religion?

1470
01:13:14,548 --> 01:13:17,135
Oh, Jesus, that's just wrong.

1471
01:13:18,053 --> 01:13:20,990
Look, nobody has to
decide anything now, okay?

1472
01:13:21,014 --> 01:13:23,767
First things first,
the pharmacy.

1473
01:13:25,310 --> 01:13:27,079
That'll be our test run.

1474
01:13:27,103 --> 01:13:27,938
Okay?

1475
01:13:38,448 --> 01:13:40,427
It's all right, Big Bill.

1476
01:13:40,451 --> 01:13:41,929
I'll bring you back
some comic books.

1477
01:13:41,953 --> 01:13:43,638
I don't want them.

1478
01:13:43,663 --> 01:13:45,933
I want you to stay here.

1479
01:13:45,957 --> 01:13:48,061
I won't be gone long.

1480
01:13:48,085 --> 01:13:49,753
It's just next door.

1481
01:13:51,254 --> 01:13:52,504
You'll be safe.

1482
01:13:53,839 --> 01:13:57,237
Daddy, Daddy, there
are things out there.

1483
01:13:57,261 --> 01:13:58,095
Things...

1484
01:13:59,221 --> 01:14:00,406
Yeah.

1485
01:14:00,430 --> 01:14:03,536
There's a lot less of
them in the daytime.

1486
01:14:03,560 --> 01:14:05,119
They'll wait.

1487
01:14:05,143 --> 01:14:06,538
They'll wait in the mist
where you can't see them,

1488
01:14:06,562 --> 01:14:09,165
and then when you go
and can't get back in,

1489
01:14:09,188 --> 01:14:10,334
they'll come and eat you up!

1490
01:14:10,358 --> 01:14:11,669
Shh.

1491
01:14:11,693 --> 01:14:13,194
Daddy, don't go!

1492
01:14:22,245 --> 01:14:23,496
I'll be back.

1493
01:14:24,832 --> 01:14:26,500
Big Bill, I promise.

1494
01:14:27,918 --> 01:14:30,730
I'll be back and then
I'm gonna take you home.

1495
01:14:30,754 --> 01:14:31,589
All right?

1496
01:14:32,423 --> 01:14:34,675
Together, we're going home.

1497
01:14:35,717 --> 01:14:37,529
If something happens,
anything at all,

1498
01:14:37,553 --> 01:14:38,989
you cut and run.

1499
01:14:39,013 --> 01:14:41,825
You get your ass back in
here, for your boy's sake.

1500
01:14:41,850 --> 01:14:43,244
If something happens to me,

1501
01:14:43,267 --> 01:14:46,705
I want you to take care of
Billy as best as you can,

1502
01:14:46,729 --> 01:14:48,457
as long as you can.

1503
01:14:48,481 --> 01:14:51,209
The Land Cruiser is yours now.

1504
01:14:51,234 --> 01:14:55,382
You get him out of here,
you just keep driving.

1505
01:14:55,406 --> 01:14:58,075
(BILLY SOBBING)

1506
01:15:00,535 --> 01:15:02,722
Where do you think you're
going, Mr. David Drayton?

1507
01:15:02,746 --> 01:15:05,517
Are you so anxious to
make your boy an orphan?

1508
01:15:05,541 --> 01:15:08,061
My boy is no concern of yours.

1509
01:15:08,085 --> 01:15:09,605
Listen up.

1510
01:15:09,629 --> 01:15:11,733
We're going to the pharmacy.

1511
01:15:11,757 --> 01:15:13,401
We're gonna bring
back some supplies.

1512
01:15:13,425 --> 01:15:17,738
Also, there may be people
trapped over there who need help.

1513
01:15:17,762 --> 01:15:19,073
Folks, listen!

1514
01:15:19,097 --> 01:15:20,825
We're not gonna
take any chances.

1515
01:15:20,849 --> 01:15:22,410
If there's any trouble,

1516
01:15:22,434 --> 01:15:24,579
we'll come straight back
here to the supermarket.

1517
01:15:24,603 --> 01:15:28,374
And bring the fiends of hell
down on our heads, thank you.

1518
01:15:28,398 --> 01:15:29,959
She's right.

1519
01:15:29,983 --> 01:15:31,669
You'll make them notice us.

1520
01:15:31,693 --> 01:15:33,672
You'll make them come.

1521
01:15:33,696 --> 01:15:36,342
Why can't you just
leave well enough alone?

1522
01:15:36,366 --> 01:15:38,344
Lady, is this what
you call well enough?

1523
01:15:38,368 --> 01:15:40,220
If you want to stop us,

1524
01:15:40,244 --> 01:15:41,472
you better explain to Bobby here

1525
01:15:41,497 --> 01:15:42,973
why we're not bringing
painkillers and medicine

1526
01:15:42,997 --> 01:15:43,892
back for his brother.

1527
01:15:43,916 --> 01:15:44,933
[BOBBY] No, I'm going.

1528
01:15:44,957 --> 01:15:46,310
Even if I have to go alone.

1529
01:15:46,334 --> 01:15:48,020
You'll die out there, young man.

1530
01:15:48,044 --> 01:15:50,649
You'll walk out that door
and be torn to shreds,

1531
01:15:50,673 --> 01:15:52,525
and then your hell-bound pride

1532
01:15:52,549 --> 01:15:54,194
will have them come
get the rest of us.

1533
01:15:54,218 --> 01:15:55,654
Yes, they'll come
back for all of us,

1534
01:15:55,678 --> 01:15:57,489
just like this good lady said.

1535
01:15:57,512 --> 01:15:59,157
Do you want that
to happen, people?

1536
01:15:59,181 --> 01:16:00,117
No!

1537
01:16:00,141 --> 01:16:01,225
No, no, no!

1538
01:16:02,643 --> 01:16:04,705
Well, it is this kind of hubris

1539
01:16:04,729 --> 01:16:06,915
that brought the wrath of
God in the first place.

1540
01:16:06,940 --> 01:16:10,126
This kind of pride
and defiance of the...

1541
01:16:10,150 --> 01:16:12,171
Shut up, you miserable buzzard!

1542
01:16:12,195 --> 01:16:13,422
You old bitch!

1543
01:16:13,446 --> 01:16:15,675
No, no, no, no, no!

1544
01:16:15,699 --> 01:16:17,635
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1545
01:16:17,659 --> 01:16:20,806
Stoning people who piss
you off is perfectly okay.

1546
01:16:20,830 --> 01:16:23,016
They do it in the
Bible, don't they?

1547
01:16:23,040 --> 01:16:24,392
And I got lots of peas.

1548
01:16:24,415 --> 01:16:27,521
David, please, if you want
to go, now's the time.

1549
01:16:27,545 --> 01:16:28,855
How bout it, Army?

1550
01:16:28,879 --> 01:16:30,816
Any help from the armed forces?

1551
01:16:30,840 --> 01:16:31,674
I'll go.

1552
01:16:34,301 --> 01:16:35,738
Jim Grondin.

1553
01:16:35,762 --> 01:16:37,323
I had you in school, didn't I?

1554
01:16:37,347 --> 01:16:39,324
Yes, me and my sister Pauline.

1555
01:16:39,348 --> 01:16:41,201
A pair of underachievers.

1556
01:16:41,224 --> 01:16:42,477
After you, Jim.

1557
01:16:43,395 --> 01:16:45,039
Yes, ma'am.

1558
01:16:45,063 --> 01:16:46,165
Shit.

1559
01:16:46,189 --> 01:16:47,417
Is that it?

1560
01:16:47,441 --> 01:16:48,960
That's everybody?

1561
01:16:48,984 --> 01:16:50,295
Everybody that's going?

1562
01:16:50,319 --> 01:16:51,463
Yes.

1563
01:16:51,487 --> 01:16:52,547
Okay.

1564
01:16:52,571 --> 01:16:55,758
Single file, one
by one, all right?

1565
01:16:55,782 --> 01:16:58,762
Let's get this thing over with.

1566
01:16:58,786 --> 01:16:59,597
Let's go.

1567
01:16:59,621 --> 01:17:00,597
After you.

1568
01:17:00,621 --> 01:17:01,456
Yes.

1569
01:17:04,417 --> 01:17:05,753
Stay together.

1570
01:17:10,339 --> 01:17:11,191
Mrs. Carmody,
you're not helping.

1571
01:17:11,215 --> 01:17:12,025
I don't care.

1572
01:17:12,049 --> 01:17:12,860
Shut the hell up!

1573
01:17:12,885 --> 01:17:14,361
You shut up!

1574
01:17:14,386 --> 01:17:16,889
(TENSE MUSIC)

1575
01:17:20,600 --> 01:17:23,079
Save the batteries.

1576
01:17:23,102 --> 01:17:25,606
(TENSE MUSIC)

1577
01:17:39,536 --> 01:17:42,373
(CREATURE GROWLS)

1578
01:18:09,277 --> 01:18:10,111
[DAVID] Shit.

1579
01:18:10,987 --> 01:18:13,419
They left the
doors propped open.

1580
01:18:14,131 --> 01:18:15,884
[OLLIE] Think something got in?

1581
01:18:17,331 --> 01:18:20,723
[DAVID] Let's just get what we
need,

1582
01:18:20,747 --> 01:18:21,808
get the hell outta here.

1583
01:18:21,832 --> 01:18:23,393
[OLLIE] Yeah, let's do that.

1584
01:18:23,417 --> 01:18:27,797
[IRENE] The meds are over at
the end there, in the cubicle.

1585
01:18:45,065 --> 01:18:47,484
